# RQ-53-20-03-070: Frame Attachment Points

## Requirement Statement
The BWB outer skin panels shall attach to circumferential frames (53-20-04) at 500mm spacing using bonded and mechanically fastened joints.

## Rationale
Load transfer from skin to frames is critical for structural integrity.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Fastener spacing: 50mm
- Fastener type: Hi-Lok titanium
- Bond strength: > 35 MPa shear
- Joint efficiency: > 90%

## Compliance Status
ICD released, joint design complete

## Traceability
Related: RQ-53-20-04-XXX (Frame requirements)
